  <description type="morphology">Stems forming dense, soft mats; branches lax, tips ascending.  Leaves divergent, not imbricate; blade linear-oblong, 3–5 × 1–2 mm, apex obtuse to broadly acute.  Pedicels to 1 cm, barely exceeding leaves at anthesis.  Flowers erect to horizontal; sepals oblong-ovate, ca. 3 mm; corolla white or tinged with pink, ca. 6 × 5 mm, lobes distinct for ca. 1/2+ their lengths, tips not recurved; stamens to 3 mm.  Capsules 4–5 mm diam.</description>
